            <bug_when>2009-05-14 19:04:39 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>fixed it by skipping the &quot;let&quot; key when initially reading the config file and temp. expanding the global let macros to replace them in e.g. the &quot;include&quot; paths. But this expansion was made permanent, which prevented re-evaluation of some macros later. This led to the issue. (with r19128)</thetext>
